X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup Make Roanoke": "https://www.meetup.com/make-roanoke/events/313528859/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_make_roanoke
X-SOURCE:Meetup Make Roanoke
UID:event_313528859@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260308T211659Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260314T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260314T160000
SUMMARY:MEMBERS ONLY: Intro to TIG Welding
DESCRIPTION:MAKE Roanoke\n**This event is for Full MAKE Roanoke Members ON
 LY.** You must have completed registration and General Orientation[ ](http
 ://makeroanoke.org/membership)[Find out more about MAKE Roanoke Membership
  here.](https://www.makeroanoke.org/become-a-member)\n\n**PLEASE READ ENTI
 RE DESCRIPTION FOR PPE REQUIREMENTS**\n\nCome learn the basics of TIG Weld
 ing at MAKE Roanoke! Students will learn about:\n\n* Safety and Terminolog
 y\n* Basic Posture and Technique\n* TIG Technique Demonstration and Practi
 ce\n\nAnd they will practice Butt or Lap joints on practice plates\, or bo
 th time permitting.\nThis class is for ages 18 and up\, and is suitable fo
 r people with no to minimal experience.\n\n***PPE Requirements (Supplied b
 y the student)***\n\n* Closed Toe Boots\n* Long Sleeve Jackets (FR\, Denim
 \, Leather\, or Cotton) **NO POLYESTER OR SYNTHETIC FIBERS**\n* Full Lengt
 h Pants\n* Safety Glasses\n* Leather working gloves or gauntlets\n\n**Plea
 se note that MAKE Roanoke is an active workshop:**\n\n* All participants m
 ust have a signed waiver on file. If the participant is a minor\, the wavi
 er must be signed by a parent or court-appointed legal guardian. [Waivers 
 can be filled out ahead of time here.](mkroa.org/waiver)\n* Closed toed sh
 oes are required in the space at all times by everyone\, regardless of age
  or participation in an event. No sandals\, crocs\, or bare feet.\n* You m
 ay be asked to remove or tuck in dangling jewelry\, lanyards\, etc for saf
 ety.\n* Depending on the activity\, other dress code rules may apply.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/make-roanoke/events/313528859/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260225T210626Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260225T210626Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup Shut Up Write": "https://www.meetup.com/shut-up-write-roanoke/events/313396356/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_shut_up_write
X-SOURCE:Meetup Shut Up Write
UID:event_313396356@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260308T211700Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260314T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260314T143000
SUMMARY:Shut Up & Write!® in Tanglewood
DESCRIPTION:Shut Up & Write!® Roanoke\nHowdy all writers of any genre and
  experience levels. I'm hosting another writing hour of dedicated silent w
 riting. Bring whatever project you got! We'll meet and socialize for 15 mi
 nutes\, spend a dedicated hour writing\, then talk about the process after
 . There is no obligation to share your work\, we're just here to get some 
 writing done in a shared space with support and just a smidge of accountab
 ility.\n\nJoin us for some focused writing time. All writers and all exper
 ience levels are welcome and don’t worry\, no one will see what you've w
 ritten. This session is about getting your writing done and meeting other 
 writers in your area.\n\nWhen you show up\, say hello to everyone\, grab a
  drink\, and get your writing tools ready. Once you’re all settled\, tak
 e some time to chat with your fellow writers. Once everyone’s arrived\, 
 I will lead quick introductions and then set the timer for our quiet and f
 ocused writing session.\n\nAfterward\, we’ll have time to chat and get t
 o know each other. We often talk about our successes and challenges as wri
 ters. If you don’t have time to stick around\, no worries!\n\nA note abo
 ut the format\nWe don’t host critiques or readings. These events are a s
 afe space for writers of all skill levels and genres to work on their craf
 t\, so no one will read or critique your writing.\n\nFor our full event sc
 hedule\, visit [shutupwrite.com](https://www.shutupwrite.com)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/shut-up-write-roanoke/events/31339635
 6/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260217T122636Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260217T122636Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup Make Roanoke": "https://www.meetup.com/make-roanoke/events/312806295/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_make_roanoke
X-SOURCE:Meetup Make Roanoke
UID:event_312806295@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260308T211659Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260314T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260314T200000
SUMMARY:MEMBERS (& Guests) ONLY: Community Craft Day
DESCRIPTION:MAKE Roanoke\nCome work on whatever project you want and enjoy
  the company of fellow MAKE Roanoke Members! Carve out some time to create
  for the sake of creating! From coloring to making hats to restoring machi
 nery\, this is a social night of crafting of all kinds for makers of all k
 inds!\n\nBring some dough to chip in for dinner if you want some!\n\nThis 
 event runs from 4-8pm and is for MAKE Roanoke members and guests.\n\n**Ple
 ase note that MAKE Roanoke is an active workshop:**\n\n* All participants 
 must have a signed waiver on file. If the participant is a minor\, the wai
 ver must be signed by a parent or court-appointed legal guardian. Waivers 
 can be filled out ahead of time at https://mkroa.org/waiver\n* Children wh
 o are not participating in the event are not permitted in the space.\n* **
 Closed toed shoes are required** in the space at all times by everyone\, r
 egardless of age or participation in an event. No sandals\, crocs\, or bar
 e feet.\n* You may be asked to remove or tuck in dangling jewelry\, lanyar
 ds\, etc. for safety.\n* Guests\, and members not signed off on yellow/red
  tools\, are only permitted to use green level tools\, but feel free to br
 ing your own tools to create something fun!
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/make-roanoke/events/312806295/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260109T191247Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260109T191247Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
