DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260320T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260320T190000
SUMMARY:Maker Mini: Multi-Material 3D Printing with Orcaslicer
DESCRIPTION:MAKE Roanoke\nJoin us at MAKE Roanoke with another FREE Maker 
 Mini as we show you techniques to achieve a multi-material or multi-color 
 3D Print!\n\nThis Maker Mini introduces the fundamentals of using OrcaSlic
 er for multi-material and multicolor 3D printing. Students will learn how 
 to assign different materials or colors to specific parts of a model\, opt
 imize print time\, and set up dissimilar material supports for clean overh
 angs. We’ll cover preparing multi-body models\, using painting tools\, a
 nd managing filament changes.\n\n**Students are encouraged to bring a lapt
 op with Orcaslicer to follow along if desired.**\n\nThis Maker Mini is FRE
 E and open to the public\, you do NOT need to be a MAKE Roanoke member to 
 attend. It is recommended for ages 14 and up.\n\n**Please note that MAKE R
 oanoke is an active workshop:**\n\n* All participants must have a signed w
 aiver on file. If the participant is a minor\, the waiver must be signed b
 y a parent or court-appointed legal guardian. Waivers can be filled out ah
 ead of time at https://mkroa.org/waiver\n* Children who are not participat
 ing in the event are not permitted in the space.\n* Closed toed shoes are 
 required in the space at all times by everyone\, regardless of age or part
 icipation in an event. No sandals\, crocs\, or bare feet.\n* You may be as
 ked to remove or tuck in dangling jewelry\, lanyards\, etc for safety.\n* 
 Depending on the activity\, other dress code rules may apply.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/make-roanoke/events/313432308/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260219T173818Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260219T173818Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Taubman Museum": "https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/event/spring-break-mini-camp/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:taubman_museum
SUMMARY:Spring Break Mini-Camp
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T123000
UID:10001949-1774085400-1774096200@www.taubmanmuseum.org
DESCRIPTION:Nancy Lorenz: The Elements LeUyen Pham (Vietnamese-American\, 
 born 1973)\, The Princess in Black and the Giant Problem\, 2020. Watercolo
 r and ink on paper © 2020 LeUyen Pham Let’s celebrate Spring Break with
  a fun morning creating art! The theme of this one-day mini-camp will be c
 entered around books. Inspired by our latest exhibition\, LeUyen Came Alon
 g: The Art of LeUyen Pham\, participants will learn about the illustrative
  art and books that LeUyen has created in her long career. Some classics y
 ou may recognize include “Vampirina Ballerina\,” “The Princess in Bl
 ack\,” and “Itty-Bitty Kitty-Corn\,” and more! Children will get to 
 create everything from a bookmark and collage to their very own book. This
  camp is for children kindergarten through fifth grade. Registration requi
 red. Members: $60 | General Public: $75 Not a member? Join today for disco
 unts on camps and classes\, exclusive invites\, free reciprocal admission 
 to the Virginia Museum of Fine Arts in Richmond\, and more. Click here to 
 learn more and become a member. Along Came LeUyen: The Art of LeUyen Pham 
 was organized by the National Center for Children’s Illustrated Literatu
 re\, Abilene\, Texas. Add to Calendar Driving? Get Directions Share This! 
 Register Now Date: Feb 04\, 2027 May 16\, 2027\n\nSource: https://www.taub
 manmuseum.org/event/spring-break-mini-camp/
LOCATION:Taubman Museum of Art\, 110 Salem Ave SE\, Roanoke\, VA\, 24011\,
  United States
URL:https://www.taubmanmuseum.org/event/spring-break-mini-camp/
X-SOURCE:Taubman Museum of Art
END:VEVENT
