SUMMARY:Intro to Home Assistant and ESPHome
DESCRIPTION:MAKE Roanoke\nMAKE Roanoke is hosting our first class on Home 
 Automation using Home Assistant!\n\nIn this class you'll learn the basics 
 of the Home Assistant smart home platform:\n\n* What it is\n* What it's us
 ed for\n* Basic Configurations\n\nAdditionally\, students will get hands-o
 n experience creating a custom smart home device with ESPHome by making a 
 Home Assistant compatible temperature and humidity sensor.\n\nStudents are
  required to bring a laptop with the Google Chrome Browser installed\, and
  a USB-A port. You can [download Google Chrome here.](https://www.google.c
 om/chrome/)\n\nThis class is open to the public\, you do NOT need to be a 
 MAKE Roanoke member to attend. It is suitable for beginners\, and is recom
 mended for ages 16 and up.\n\nThe cost to attend is $45\, and the cost for
  MAKE Roanoke members is $35. MAKE Roanoke members can also bring one gues
 t at the discounted member rate!\n\n**Please note that MAKE Roanoke is an 
 active workshop:**\n\n* All participants must have a signed waiver on file
 . If the participant is a minor\, the waiver must be signed by a parent or
  court-appointed legal guardian. Waivers can be filled out ahead of time a
 t [https://mkroa.org/waiver](https://mkroa.org/waiver "https://mkroa.org/w
 aiver")\n* Children who are not participating in the event are not permitt
 ed in the space.\n* Closed toed shoes are required in the space at all tim
 es by everyone\, regardless of age or participation in an event. No sandal
 s\, crocs\, or bare feet.\n* You may be asked to remove or tuck in danglin
 g jewelry\, lanyards\, etc for safety.\n* Depending on the activity\, othe
 r dress code rules may apply.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/make-roanoke/events/313432537/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260219T180837Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260219T180837Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
