DESCRIPTION:Nancy Lorenz: The Elements Join us as we explore the Taubman M
 useum of Art! This session is designed for participants 10 years and older
  and their families or caretakers with specific adaptations for those who 
 identify as: Blind or have low vision Deaf or hard of hearing Neurodiverse
  (Autism Spectrum\, Sensory Processing\, Learning Disabilities) Living wit
 h Intellectual and Developmental Disabilities In each Happy HeARTs session
 \, participants focus on a particular work of art in the galleries and tak
 e part in an art activity that is accessible and sensory-friendly. Partici
 pants also have the opportunity to explore the Museum’s interactive gall
 ery\, Art Venture. Free and welcoming\, though registration is highly enco
 uraged. Contact Katrina King-Singh at kking@taubmanmuseum.org or 540-204-4
 131 with any questions and to learn more about this free program. Add to C
 alendar Driving? Get Directions Share This! Register Now This program is m
 ade possible through funding from the Institute of Museum and Library Serv
 ices. Date: Feb 04\, 2027 May 16\, 2027\n\nSource: https://www.taubmanmuse
 um.org/happy-hearts-community-session-ages-10-and-older-march-28
