BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Roanoke Symphony": "https://rso.com/event/magnificat/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:roanoke_symphony
X-SOURCE:Roanoke Symphony
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260412T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260412T163000
DTSTAMP:20260308T105647
CREATED:20250627T134133Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251013T145449Z
UID:10000068-1776006000-1776011400@rso.com
SUMMARY:Magnificat
DESCRIPTION:The versatile performers of the RSO and Chorus present the splendor and devotional richness of the Baroque era. Handel’s Music for the Royal Fireworks dazzles with its bold brass and was written to accompany a grand celebration in London’s Green Park. Vivaldi’s Gloria\, is a joyful and spirited work filled with vibrant contrasts and lyrical beauty sure to uplift. J.S. Bach’s brilliant Magnificat is a masterful setting of the Virgin Mary’s song of praise\, blending intricate counterpoint with exuberant choruses\, virtuoso trumpet solos\, and joyful choral writing. \nDavid Stewart Wiley\, conductor\nRoanoke Symphony Chorus\nJohn Hugo\, chorus master \nGeorge Frideric Handel: Selections from Music for The Royal Fireworks\nAntonio Vivaldi: Gloria\, RV589\nJ.S. Bach: Magnificat\, BWV 243 in D Major \nThanks to our Sponsors!
URL:https://rso.com/event/magnificat/
LOCATION:Berglund Performing Arts Theatre\, 710 Williamson Rd NE\, Roanoke\, VA\, 24016\, United States
CATEGORIES:Masterworks
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://rso.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/seasons-art-elements5.jpg
END:VEVENT
