BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup Roanoke Valley Net": "https://www.meetup.com/roanoke-valley-net-user-group/events/313580154/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_roanoke_valley_net
X-SOURCE:Meetup Roanoke Valley Net
UID:event_313580154@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260308T211700Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260507T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260507T200000
SUMMARY:Online: The 1-Person DevOps Stack presentation by Lionel Sapp
DESCRIPTION:Roanoke Valley .NET User Group (RVNUG)\nThe 1-Person DevOps St
 ack: How I Keep Client Apps Alive Without a Big Team presented by Lionel S
 app.\n\nWhen you're a solo builder\, "DevOps" isn't a department — it's 
 whatever keeps production stable at 11pm when a client pings you and real 
 users are stuck. In this TED-style talk\, I'll share the minimal\, battle-
 tested operations stack I use to ship and maintain client apps without a b
 ig team: preview deployments for safe releases\, error tracking and loggin
 g that actually matter\, and a calm incident loop for when something break
 s. I'll also show how AI fits in practically (not hype): using v0 for rapi
 d UI mockups and Cursor/MCP agents to speed up implementation while keepin
 g quality guardrails in place. The stack is modern\, simple\, and repeatab
 le — Next.js + Supabase + Vercel + Resend + Stripe — but the real valu
 e is the workflow: what to monitor (and what to ignore)\, how to deploy wi
 th confidence\, and the "stability rituals" that keep apps alive long afte
 r launch.\n\nThis is an online talk.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/roanoke-valley-net-user-group/events/
 313580154/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260301T004309Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260301T004309Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
